35.37	Throne	Throne	A throne is the seat of state of a potentate or dignitary, especially the seat occupied by a sovereign on state occasions; or the seat occupied by a pope or bishop on ceremonial occasions. "Throne" in an abstract sense can also refer to the monarchy or the Crown itself, an instance of metonymy, and is also used in many expressions such as "the power behind the throne".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cc/Canada_senate_chairs.jpg/250px-Canada_senate_chairs.jpg
